history.content:
EECS 47D (read post @5578) is what you'd take if you just want to do the circuits portion of 16A. 

imo 16A's linear algebra is more application-driven than what Math 54 teaches (read:Math 54 but word problems), so if you don't feel comfortable self-teaching that (since you have to take the 16A final) you might want to just take 16A. I've also heard students taking 47D get somewhat overwhelmed effectively adding a 4 unit course in the middle of the semester, so if you do go that route, make sure the rest of your schedule isn't too packed.

I have already taken math 54 before deciding to major in CS. Would you recommend me to retake EE16A, or self-study the circuit part and only take EE16B? Is there any class that only teaches the circuit that could also satisfy the requirement of EE16A? (I heard there's one but I forgot which one is it)
Thank you for your answer!
